<p>Grantee agrees and consents to this Grant Agreement (the "Agreement"), which includes: (1) this "Grant Agreement Terms and Conditions," (2) the attached "China Sustainable Energy Program Standard Conditions," <%= ga_proposal_and_budget_date %>, <%=request_project_summary %>. 
These documents are attached hereto and incorporated herein by this reference.</p>

<p>Grantee shall use this grant solely for the purposes outlined in the attached proposal description and it is understood that these grant funds will be used for such purposes in accordance with the budget submitted. Grantee shall repay to the Energy Foundation any portion of the amount granted which is not used for the purposes of this grant.</p>

<p>The grantee agrees that no funds provided pursuant to this Grant Agreement may be used to contact, or urge the public to contact, members of a legislative body for the purpose of proposing, supporting, or opposing legislation; or to advocate the adoption or rejection of legislation.  See Treasury Regulation section 1.501(c)(3)-1(c)(3)(ii).</p>

<p>Grantee shall submit to the Energy Foundation narrative progress reports and financial progress reports, according to the reporting schedule which follows.</p>

<p class='page-break'>The interim reports should set forth (a) a brief description of progress to date toward completing the work
described in the proposal, and (b) how the proceeds of the grant have been spent to date i.e., a financial
report showing actual expenditures according to the budget categories as originally proposed.</p>

<p>The Energy Foundation will require a final report (including a final narrative and financial report) at the end of the project. The final reports, both narrative and financial, shall be due no later than one month after the termination of the grant period. The financial report should show revenues and expenses for both this grant and the project. Clearly show the amount funded by the Energy Foundation and how these funds have been spent according to the categories of the initial budget. Use three columns for the report:</p>

<table>
<tr><td width='40'></td><td width='75' valign="top">Column 1 -</td><td valign="top">Present the entire project budget (all sources of revenue and expenditures) as included in the original proposal;</td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td valign="top">Column 2 -</td><td valign="top">Present the actual revenue and expenditures for the project in total;</td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td valign="top">Column 3 -</td><td valign="top">Present the actual revenue and expenditures funded by the Energy Foundation grant only.</td></tr>
</table>

<p>Reports are due as follows:</p>

<table>
