<p>Grantee ensures that grant funds under this award will be used in compliance with all applicable antiterrorist financing and asset control laws, regulations, rules, and executive orders. Grantee also agrees to take all reasonable precautions to ensure that any person or group expected to receive money from the grantee will neither make any payment nor provide any material support to any person on any United States government list of suspected terrorists.</p>

<p>Grantee shall not use any portion of the funds granted to influence specific legislation, to engage in private profit-making or private gain, nor for any non-charitable or non-educational purpose and will include a positive disclaimer stating that no Energy Foundation funds were used for lobbying purposes on all narrative and financial reports.</p>

<p>Grantee shall notify the Energy Foundation of any organizational changes during the term of the grant, including, but not limited to, changes in key personnel, changes in tax status, and changes in project timing. The grantee is responsible for completing the agreed deliverables in a diligent and timely manner.  At the discretion of the grantee, significant changes affecting these deliverables can be proposed to the Energy Foundation for discussion and endorsement. Changes requiring transfers between budget categories must be approved in advance by the Energy Foundation.</p>

<p>Grantee shall permit representatives of the Energy Foundation to visit the premises and review the activities of the Grantee with respect to the programs supported by this grant.</p>

<p>Grantee may announce receipt of this grant.  Please furnish the Energy Foundation with a copy in advance of this announcement.</p>

<p>Please refer to grant number <b><%= fluxx_request.grant_id %></b> in all future correspondence and reports which relate to this grant.</p>

<p>The board and staff of the Energy Foundation are pleased to be able to make this grant to your organization.  Please sign and return one copy of this grant agreement as evidence of your understanding and agreement with the terms and conditions defined in this letter.</p>


